 134:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** * Function Name: USBFS_DEBUG_Start
 135:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** ****************************************************************************//**
 136:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 137:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   This function performs all required initialization for the USBFS component.
 138:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   After this function call, the USB device initiates communication with the
ARM GAS  C:\Users\yoons\AppData\Local\Temp\ccJHkSRb.s 			page 4


 139:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   host by pull-up D+ line. This is the preferred method to begin component
 140:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   operation.
 141:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 142:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   Note that global interrupts have to be enabled because interrupts are
 143:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   required for USBFS component operation.
 144:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 145:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   PSoC 4200L devices: when USBFS component configured to DMA with Automatic
 146:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   Buffer Management, the DMA interrupt priority is changed to the highest
 147:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   (priority 0) inside this function.
 148:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 149:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   PSoC 3/PSoC 5LP devices: when USBFS component configured to DMA with
 150:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   Automatic Buffer Management, the Arbiter interrupt priority is changed to
 151:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   the highest (priority 0) inside this function.
 152:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 153:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param device
 154:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *          Contains the device number of the desired device descriptor.
 155:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *          The device number can be found in the Device Descriptor Tab of
 156:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *          "Configure" dialog, under the settings of desired Device Descriptor,
 157:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *          in the "Device Number" field.
 158:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param mode:
 159:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   The operating voltage. This determines whether the voltage regulator
 160:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   is enabled for 5V operation or if pass through mode is used for 3.3V
 161:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   operation. Symbolic names and their associated values are given in the
 162:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   following list.
 163:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 164:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *       *USBFS_DEBUG_3V_OPERATION* - Disable voltage regulator and pass-
 165:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *                                      through Vcc for pull-up
 166:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 167:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *       *USBFS_DEBUG_5V_OPERATION* - Enable voltage regulator and use
 168:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *                                      regulator for pull-up
 169:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 170:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *       *USBFS_DEBUG_DWR_POWER_OPERATION* - Enable or disable the voltage
 171:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *                                      regulator depending on the power supply
 172:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *                                      voltage configuration in the DWR tab.
 173:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *                                      For PSoC 3/5LP devices, the VDDD supply
 174:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *                                      voltage is considered and for PSoC 4A-L,
 175:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *                                      the VBUS supply voltage is considered.*
 176:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** * \globalvars
 177:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \ref USBFS_DEBUG_initVar
 178:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 179:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** * \sideeffect
 180:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   This function will reset all communication states to default.
 181:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 182:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** * \reentrant
 183:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  No.
 184:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
 185:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *******************************************************************************/
