1609:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** ****************************************************************************//**
1610:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1611:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   This function performs different functionality depending on the Component’s
1612:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   configured Endpoint Buffer Management. This parameter is defined in the
1613:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   Descriptor Root in Component Configure window.
1614:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1615:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   *Manual (Static/Dynamic Allocation):*
1616:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   This function moves the specified number of bytes from endpoint buffer to
1617:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   system RAM. The number of bytes actually transferred from endpoint buffer to
1618:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   system RAM is the lesser of the actual number of bytes sent by the host or
1619:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   the number of bytes requested by the length parameter.
1620:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1621:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   *DMA with Manual Buffer Management:*
1622:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   Configure DMA to transfer data from endpoint buffer to system RAM. Generate
1623:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   a DMA request. The firmware must wait until the DMA completes the data
1624:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   transfer after calling the USBFS_DEBUG_ReadOutEP() API. For example,
1625:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   by checking EPstate:
1626:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1627:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   \snippet /USBFS_sut_02.cydsn/main.c checking EPstatey
1628:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1629:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   The USBFS_EnableOutEP() has to be called to allow host to write data into
1630:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   the endpoint buffer after DMA has completed transfer data from OUT endpoint
1631:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   buffer to SRAM.
1632:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1633:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   *DMA with Automatic Buffer Management:*
1634:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   Configure DMA. This is required only once and automatically generates DMA
1635:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   requests as data arrives
1636:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1637:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param epNumber: Contains the data endpoint number.
1638:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *            Valid values are between 1 and 8.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\yoons\AppData\Local\Temp\ccJHkSRb.s 			page 51


1639:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param pData: A pointer to a data array from which the data for the endpoint
1640:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *         space is loaded.
1641:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param length: The number of bytes to transfer from the USB Out endpoint and
1642:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *          loads it into data array. Valid values are between 0 and 1023. The
1643:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *          function moves fewer than the requested number of bytes if the host
1644:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *          sends fewer bytes than requested.
1645:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1646:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** * \return
1647:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  Number of bytes received, 0 for an invalid endpoint.
