1831:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1832:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  This function performs different functionality depending on the Component’s
1833:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  configured Endpoint Buffer Management. This parameter is defined in
1834:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  the Descriptor Root in Component Configure window.
1835:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1836:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  *Manual (Static/Dynamic Allocation):*
1837:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  This function loads and enables the specified USB data endpoint for an IN
1838:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  data transfer.
1839:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1840:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  *DMA with Manual Buffer Management:*
1841:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  Configures DMA for a data transfer from system RAM to endpoint buffer.
1842:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  Generates request for a transfer.
1843:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1844:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  *DMA with Automatic Buffer Management:*
1845:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  Configures DMA. This is required only once, so it is done only when parameter
1846:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  pData is not NULL. When the pData pointer is NULL, the function skips this
1847:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  task. Sets Data ready status: This generates the first DMA transfer and
1848:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  prepares data in endpoint buffer.
1849:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1850:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param epNumber Contains the data endpoint number.
1851:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *        Valid values are between 1 and 8.
1852:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param *pData A pointer to a data array from which the data for the endpoint
1853:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *        space is loaded. It shall be ensured that this pointer address is even
1854:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *        to ensure the 16-bit transfer is aligned to even address. Else, a hard
1855:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *        fault condition can occur.
1856:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param length The number of bytes to transfer from the array and then send as
1857:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *        a result of an IN request. Valid values are between 0 and 512 (1023 for
1858:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *        DMA with Automatic Buffer Management mode). The value 512 is applicable
1859:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *        if only one endpoint is used.
1860:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1861:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** * \reentrant
1862:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  No.
1863:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
1864:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *******************************************************************************/
