2063:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
2064:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   *Manual (Static/Dynamic Allocation):*
2065:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   This function moves the specified number of bytes from endpoint buffer to
2066:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   system RAM. The number of bytes actually transferred from endpoint buffer to
2067:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   system RAM is the lesser of the actual number of bytes sent by the host or
2068:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   the number of bytes requested by the length parameter.
2069:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
2070:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   *DMA with Manual Buffer Management:*
2071:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   Configure DMA to transfer data from endpoint buffer to system RAM. Generate
2072:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   a DMA request. The firmware must wait until the DMA completes the data
2073:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   transfer after calling the USBFS_DEBUG_ReadOutEP() API. For example,
2074:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   by checking EPstate:
2075:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
2076:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   \snippet /USBFS_sut_02.cydsn/main.c checking EPstatey
2077:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
2078:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   The USBFS_EnableOutEP() has to be called to allow host to write data into
2079:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   the endpoint buffer after DMA has completed transfer data from OUT endpoint
2080:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   buffer to SRAM.
2081:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
2082:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   *DMA with Automatic Buffer Management:*
2083:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   Configure DMA. This is required only once and automatically generates DMA
2084:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *   requests as data arrives
2085:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *
2086:Generated_Source\PSoC5/USBFS_DEBUG.c **** *  \param epNumber: Contains the data endpoint number.
